<p><strong>Registration</strong></p>
<p>Please <a href="https://wimr.snapforms.com.au/form/registration?new%20patient=[PATIENT]&adult%20or%20paed=Adult&research%20or%20clinic=Clinic&consult%20or%20sleep=Consult&first%20name=[FIRST_NAME]&last%20name=[LAST_NAME]&dob=[DOB]">click here</a> and complete your registration form before attending for your appointment.</p>
<p><strong>Before your appointment</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>The attached Patient Registration Form and Consent Form needs to be completed and returned to <a href="mailto:reception@woolcock.org.au">reception@woolcock.org.au</a> prior to your appointment.</li>
<li>Please email your referral to <a href="mailto:reception@woolcock.org.au">reception@woolcock.org.au</a> prior to your appointment. Note:</li>
</ol>
<ul>
<li><em>A specialist referral is valid for 3 months and a GP referral is valid for 12 months. Without a valid referral at the time of your consultation/treatment, Medicare will not be able to process your claim.</em></li>
<li><em>Approval documentation from your Insurer needs to be provided in the case of a Workers&rsquo; Compensation or Third-Party Claim. If not supplied, payment will need to be made on the day by the patient. </em></li>
</ul>
<ol>
<li>You will receive a confirmation SMS 72 hours before your appointment. To secure your appointment, you must SMS &lsquo;Yes&rdquo; to confirm your attendance.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>What to bring:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Medicare card/Pensioner card/Concession card/DVA card/Centrelink Health Care card</li>
<li>Test results (for example, blood tests, X-rays, scans)</li>
<li>Medication list</li>
<li>During the COVID pandemic, please ensure that you wear a mask at the clinic. This will help to ensure the safety and wellbeing of yourself and everyone you come in contact with at the clinic.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong><u>&nbsp;</u></strong></p>
<p><strong>COVID-19:</strong></p>
<p><strong>Have you:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Been diagnosed with COVID-19?</li>
<li>Had any respiratory <a href="https://www.health.nsw.gov.au/Infectious/covid-19/Pages/frequently-asked-questions.aspx#1-4">symptomsâ€‹</a>&nbsp;in the last 7 days:</li>
<ul>
<li>fever (37.5&deg; or higher)</li>
<li>cough</li>
<li>sore throat</li>
<li>shortness of breath (difficulty breathing)</li>
<li>runny nose</li>
<li>loss of taste</li>
<li>loss of smell.</li>
</ul>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>If you have answered YES to any of the above questions, please call us to reschedule your appointment. Please wear a mask when entering the clinic. Thank you for your cooperation.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>IMPORTANT NOTICE:</strong></p>
<p>The Woolcock Institute has implemented measures to ensure both your safety and the safety of its staff and Doctors.&nbsp; Patients who attend the Woolcock for an overnight Sleep Study, face to face CPAP review, or Lung Function Test will require either:</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<ol>
<li>A negative COVID PCR test be performed within 48 hours of attending the Clinic; or</li>
<li>A negative rapid antigen test (RAT) be performed at the Clinic by the patient using their own RAT kit under supervision; or</li>
<li>A negative rapid antigen test (RAT) be administered by one of our trained staff upon arrival at the Clinic. &nbsp;A $12 charge for the RAT kit will apply.</li>
</ol>
<p>Please attend 20 minutes beforehand to complete the test.&nbsp; If you test positive at the Woolcock Clinic, you will be asked to return home immediately and follow NSW Health guidelines. We will reschedule your appointment.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Payment/cancellation:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Payment:</strong>&nbsp;The cost of your initial consultation is $400.00. If other services are required on the day, additional fees are payable.</li>
</ul>
<p>We accept EFTPOS, credit cards including AMEX without surcharge (no Diners Club), or cash. We can submit your claim to Medicare on site, given there is a valid referral and Medicare details.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Please note that as a private clinic Dr Blackwell doesn&rsquo;t Bulk Bill as a rule.</strong></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><strong>Cancellation or Change:</strong>&nbsp;Please provide at least 2 working days&rsquo; notice if you need to cancel or change your booking.&nbsp;This will enable a person on our waiting list to be contacted.&nbsp;If you do not provide this notice, you will be charged an out-of-pocket cancellation fee of at least $100.00.</li>
</ul>
